      "id": "PopularPost101170",
      "post_content": "This could have its uses, especially on black-red which, coincidentially, have some if not the best 187 creatures (almost all Rats, [Avalanche Riders](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Avalanche Riders), [Keldon Champion](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Keldon Champion), [Ingot Chewer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ingot Chewer), [Nekrataal](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Nekrataal), [Shriekmaw](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shriekmaw), [Flametongue Kavu](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flametongue Kavu)... and on the other hand, [Spark Elemental](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Spark Elemental), [Hellspark Elemental](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hellspark Elemental), [Ball Lightning](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ball Lightning), [Blistering Firecat](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blistering Firecat). And this is just from the top of my head).   \nSadly, it competes with lots of better 3-drops on its colors. A 3/2 for ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol) would have been a lot better.",
